<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>So we basicly disagree on nothing.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Min">Min</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:27 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> So we basicly disagree on nothing.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=740" TARGET=_self>Re: And have you, Sir, made any contribution besides criticize and criticize?</A> (dylan waite)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> i argue that the solution is NOT more open PK like everyone

<BR>&gt; seems to want but, actually, more newbie saving
<BR>&gt; restrictions....Verant will never take rampant UO-style PvP
<BR>&gt; seriously
<P>People wants open PK are more vocal, but I think the majority prefer switch.
<P>&gt; maybe my vision is skewed here as i seem to have been sucked
<BR>&gt; right into the middle of it...but i DO notice an inordinate
<BR>&gt; amount of flaming going on here...i'm surprised people haven't
<BR>&gt; started e-mail bombing each other yet
<P>I've been playing multplayer games for too long that I automaticly ignore Rand/Whitewolf type posts.
<P>&gt; i didn't say he preferred UO refugees......i only said i don't
<BR>&gt; know where he stands...on ANYTHING
<P>Well that's for him to answer, and as a GM you basicly have to be neutral, I am certain he has his own opinions but he wants to keep as open-minded as possible.
<P>&gt; i'm afraid i missed that....given everything i heard during beta
<BR>&gt; i have a hard time believing Verant is considering doing away
<BR>&gt; with the level/skill system....i think you likely misunderstood
<BR>&gt; geiger here, or he misunderstood your question
<P>Again that's for them to decide I have no power to enforce anything.
<P>&gt; honestly, i have not ......my problem is not going to be with
<BR>&gt; the +PvP people on the normal servers, my problem is with the
<BR>&gt; +PvP server which the players seem to want to turn in the
<BR>&gt; apocolyptic battle at the end of time.....very few people, i
<BR>&gt; think, want this but it only takes a few rampant pk's to bring
<BR>&gt; the general populace down to their level....the situation will
<BR>&gt; erode until we do, really, have EverQuake....this is my worst
<BR>&gt; nightmare an i don't want to see it happen....my advice is to
<BR>&gt; (since banning them is a bit draconian) cripple the ability of
<BR>&gt; the k3wLd00d to be disruptive....not less rstriction on PvP,
<BR>&gt; MORE.......then maybe Verant's vision of legitimate PvP can be
<BR>&gt; realized
<P>Well you have an option not to join the +PvP server, on regular servers you can still find plenty of +PvP like me, you said yourself that very few people want the apocolyptic mass killing and those few people will be populating the +PvP server which leaves the majority of more mature +PvP players on the regular server, it's not like PvP is dead.
<P>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
